snippet: A record-breaking storm that dumped four feet of snow in western South Dakota left tens of thousands of people without electricity on Monday and ranchers bracing for heavy losses.
abstract: Record-breaking storm dumps four feet of snow in western South Dakota, leaving tens of thousands of people without electricity and ranchers bracing for heavy losses.
